HEADWORD: Sneaking
<hw>Sneak"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Marked by cowardly concealment;
deficient in openness and courage; underhand; mean; crouching.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Sneak"ing*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sneak"ing*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

